Details: Maya Academy of Advanced Cinematics (MAAC) is India's foremost institute for excellence in the field of animation and computer graphics. We take great pride in our intuitive philosophy of evolving over strong conceptual knowledge, which enables us to focus, more on talents conceptual base before evolving on to its practical sciences. The 3D animation and visual effects industry in India has become one of the hottest industries with the Govt. of India lending full support by way of recognising the entertainment industry and with NASSCOM putting positive figures and optimism on its growth. MAAC offers the most advanced environment to its students in terms of infrastructure, academic curriculum, and seasoned professionals as faculties for cultivating creative skills and knowledge in animation and computer graphics. The institute stands out from the rest by providing the best exposure to the international animation industry. Hence, it allows the students to get exposed to the latest development and technology all over the world. MAAC is also credited with being the largest Auto Desk Authorized Training Centers (ATC), the global leaders in animation software. On an average, MAAC trains 11,000 students every year, providing them with a true-to-studio study environment, state-of-the-art infrastructure facility, an extensive curriculum, and the benefit of a highly experienced faculty.Placements by MAAC & its contribution to the Indian animation industry: The animation industry offers career opportunities in a range of activities - from technology-based jobs such as scanning, compositing, digital ink and paint, and game designing to creative guys like visual-effects supervisors, 3D modellers, and character animators.MAAC offers a highly integrated curriculum to its students from the initial sketching phase to the final on-screen animation phase, helping in building a talent pool of studio-ready students, who can confidently fill up the growing gap between demand and supply of quality animators. Moreover, strongly networked placement division helps its students secure credible placements at various animation studios and allied sectors. Valued production houses like Rhythm & Hues, Crest Communication, Pixion, Prana, Tata Elxsi, U TV, Ani-rights, Prime Focus, Data Quest, etc., conduct campus interviews at MAAC centres and absorb students even before they have completed the course. These production houses are majority catering to international projects from different parts of the globe outsourced to Indian animation market.New courses introduced at MAAC: To move on with the international animation market, MAAC has always been in the process of upgrading its course structure to service future demand and based on the feedback from production experts, we have optimised and introduced new technologies and applications in our new programAD3D. It is designed keeping in mind the latest trends in production techniques and technologies used in top studios and production houses.As you are looking for a short-term course/specialized animation course/career course, we suggest you visit our website: www.maacindia.com. Branch: A-302, Ganesh Plaza, Near Navrangpura Post Office, Opposite Navrangpura Bus stand, Off C.G. Road, Ahmadabad -380009

Details: Maya Academy of Advanced Cinematics (MAAC) is India's foremost institute for excellence in the field of animation and computer graphics. We take great pride in our intuitive philosophy of evolving over strong conceptual knowledge, which enables us to focus, more on talents conceptual base before evolving on to its practical sciences. The 3D animation and visual effects industry in India has become one of the hottest industries with the Govt. of India lending full support by way of recognising the entertainment industry and with NASSCOM putting positive figures and optimism on its growth. MAAC offers the most advanced environment to its students in terms of infrastructure, academic curriculum, and seasoned professionals as faculties for cultivating creative skills and knowledge in animation and computer graphics. The institute stands out from the rest by providing the best exposure to the international animation industry. Hence, it allows the students to get exposed to the latest development and technology all over the world. MAAC is also credited with being the largest Auto Desk Authorized Training Centers (ATC), the global leaders in animation software. On an average, MAAC trains 11,000 students every year, providing them with a true-to-studio study environment, state-of-the-art infrastructure facility, an extensive curriculum, and the benefit of a highly experienced faculty.Placements by MAAC & its contribution to the Indian animation industry: The animation industry offers career opportunities in a range of activities - from technology-based jobs such as scanning, compositing, digital ink and paint, and game designing to creative guys like visual-effects supervisors, 3D modellers, and character animators.MAAC offers a highly integrated curriculum to its students from the initial sketching phase to the final on-screen animation phase, helping in building a talent pool of studio-ready students, who can confidently fill up the growing gap between demand and supply of quality animators. Moreover, strongly networked placement division helps its students secure credible placements at various animation studios and allied sectors. Valued production houses like Rhythm & Hues, Crest Communication, Pixion, Prana, Tata Elxsi, U TV, Ani-rights, Prime Focus, Data Quest, etc., conduct campus interviews at MAAC centres and absorb students even before they have completed the course. These production houses are majority catering to international projects from different parts of the globe outsourced to Indian animation market.New courses introduced at MAAC: To move on with the international animation market, MAAC has always been in the process of upgrading its course structure to service future demand and based on the feedback from production experts, we have optimised and introduced new technologies and applications in our new programAD3D. It is designed keeping in mind the latest trends in production techniques and technologies used in top studios and production houses.As you are looking for a short-term course/specialized animation course/career course, we suggest you visit our website: www.maacindia.com. Details:
Synergy focuses on training individuals on project management concepts and software tools such as Microsoft Office Project, MSP Server, Primavera, and Primavera Complete, Asta Power Project. The courses will be offered in 70 locations across India and in 7 countries, as listed in its website. 
Synergy also trains on PMP Certification Preparatory module, and conducts PME (Project Management Expert) Certification for PM Aspirants.

The School will also help students find employment in the relevant corporate firms for the respective programs.
